<div class="project-text">
    <h3>The Project</h3>
    <p>A passion became a job, and the job became an entire world of people and new experiences. Andreea got into crocheting amigurumi in the summer of 2024. By October we were at every craft market in the area, every weekend. In a short time we had produced dozens of patterns for anyone who wanted to make the same figures by hand, all available on Gumroad or printed and sold in person.</p>
    <p>Collaborations, fairs, workshops. I have worked for many people met along the way, all artisans who wanted a small online presence or just to communicate better on their social channels. Being around them also led me to discover my own crafty side: I make candles, nothing serious, just something to do with my hands when I need to slow down.</p>
    <p>Each pattern, as they are called, was made entirely by hand including the digital version. Every one was personalized to match the character's mood, with hundreds of step-by-step photos shot in a lightbox, and instructions written to be clear for anyone regardless of experience.</p>
    <p>Today I share my office with several boxes containing hundreds of handmade figures, and almost everyone I know owns at least one and often orders more as gifts.</p>
